onal Website(s), and is under no obligation to accept any Website(s), even if the additional Website(s) is the property of an already approved Publisher.  All activity for a given account will be consolidated into one report. \r\n\r\n(b)  Site_Name Websites: For purposes of this Agreement, all Websites that are owned, operated or hosted by or on behalf of Site_Name, are referred to herein collectively as the "Site_Name Websites." You agree that you will not use the Site_Name Websites or any content therein or data obtained therefrom for any purposes other than to fulfill this Agreement and that you will not disseminate any of the information contained on Site_Name Websites, without prior consent from Site_Name . You agree that you will not use any automated means, including, without limitation, agents, robots, scripts, or spiders, to access or manage your account with Site_Name or to monitor or copy the Site_Name Websites or the content contained therein except via automated means expressly made available by Site_Name , if any, or authorized in advance and in writing by Site_Name (for example, Site_Name -approved third-party tools and services). You will not interfere or attempt to interfere with the proper working of the Site_Name Websites or any program thereon, or the Site_Name System. Without limitation to the foregoing, you further agree that you will not take any action that imposes an unreasonable or disproportionately large load on the Site_Name Websites, any programs thereon, or Site_Name ''s infrastructure, as determined by Site_Name .\r\n\r\n(c) Services: Publisher understands and agrees that from time to time the Site_Name System hereunder may be inaccessible, unavailable or inoperable for any reason, including, without limitation: (i) equipment malfunctions; (ii) periodic maintenance procedures or repairs which Site_Name may undertake from time to time; or (iii) causes beyond the control of Site_Name or which are not reasonably foreseeable by Site_Name, including, without limitation, interruption or failure of telecommunication or digital transmission links, hostile network attacks, the unavailability, operation, or inaccessibility of Websites or interfaces, network congestion or other failures. While Site_Name will attempt to provide the services on a continuous basis, Publisher acknowledges and agrees that Site_Name has no control over the availability of the services on a continuous or uninterrupted basis. Publisher also understands and agrees that Site_Name is not responsible for the functionality of any third-party Website or interface. Terms of this Agreement are subject to Site_Name hardware, software, and bandwidth traffic limitations. Failure to deliver because of technical difficulties does not represent a failure to meet the obligations of this Agreement. Site_Name reserves the right to discontinue offering any of the Site_Name Systems and/or Site_Name Websites at any time. Except as otherwise specified by Site_Name, Publisher agrees that it will direct all communications relating to any Site_Name Website or your participation therein directly to Site_Name and not to any other entity.\r\n2. Website Content and Prohibited Conduct \r\n(a) Pre-approval Required: Publishers that have Websites that relate to or have any characteristic of the following shall be approved on a case by case basis: (i) excessive ads, app  quest/test, user content (blogs, etc.), (ii) controversial issues, religion, sexual orientation and/or edgy humor, (iii) wrestling, (iv) anime, (v) old content, and/or (vi) poor quality design and functionality.\r\n\r\n(b) Prohibited Conduct: Site_Name does not accept Websites that produce, relate to or have characteristics of Prohibited Conduct. Prohibited Conduct is defined as: \r\n(i) Ad Placement & Tracking: Publisher shall not: (1) Place Creatives or Ads in emails without prior consent and tracking from Site_Name; (2) Intentionally place Creatives on blank web pages or on web pages with no 